
wnload the latest version of the elastic search from here -
http://github.com/downloads/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-*.tar.gz

Unpack the tar file in the download directory. This should create a directory "~/Downloads/elasticsearch-*"

Pull down the elastic search service wrapper from Github.

<code>
cd ~/Downloads 
</code>
<code>
git clone https://github.com/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-servicewrapper.git elasticsearch-servicewrapper
</code>
 
Now we will move the service into place

<code>cd ~/Downloads</code>
<code>sudo mv elasticsearch-* /use/local/share</code>
<code>cd elasticsearch-servicewrapper</code>
<code>sudo mv service /usr/local/share/elasticsearch-*/bin</code>
<code>cd /usr/local/share</code>
<code>sudo ln -s elasticsearch-* elastic search</code>
<code>sudo chown -R root:wheel elasticsearch</code>

Now start up the service
<code>
cd /usr/local/share/elasticsearch</code>

<code>sudo bin/service/elasticsearch start</code>
